1
00:00:37,291 --> 00:00:38,833
[birds chirping]

2
00:00:51,916 --> 00:00:53,833
[OGATA] Looks like
they're nowhere near us.

3
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:57,083
This is probably too optimistic,

4
00:00:57,166 --> 00:00:59,583
but maybe that weather
was too much for the Seventh.

5
00:00:59,666 --> 00:01:02,833
I can't see them giving up
and going home, though, can you?

6
00:01:02,916 --> 00:01:05,291
No, they're expecting us.

7
00:01:05,375 --> 00:01:08,166
They think we'll head down
the mountains towards Abashiri.

8
00:01:08,250 --> 00:01:09,750
So we'll do the unexpected

9
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:11,833
and head towards
Tokachi to shake them off.

10
00:01:11,916 --> 00:01:13,500
[ASIRPA]
Let's go.

11
00:01:13,583 --> 00:01:15,416
The others know what to do.

12
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:18,541
If separated,
we meet up in Abashiri.

13
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:24,041
I sent Huci a telegram.

14
00:01:24,125 --> 00:01:25,375
I wanted to check in with her

15
00:01:25,458 --> 00:01:28,125
and make sure everything
there was all right.

16
00:01:28,208 --> 00:01:29,708
There should be an answer
waiting for us

17
00:01:29,791 --> 00:01:31,250
at this post office.

18
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:33,416
Who from?

19
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:35,416
From Asirpa's uncle.

20
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,458
He used to work
with the Japanese for a time,

21
00:01:37,541 --> 00:01:39,791
so he knows how to read
and write a little.

22
00:01:42,166 --> 00:01:43,875
[CIKIAPASI]
What does it say?

23
00:01:43,958 --> 00:01:47,041
"Huci making raikurushiyuku."

24
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:50,708
What's "raikurushiyuku"?

25
00:01:50,791 --> 00:01:51,916
[INKARMAT]
Raykur Siyuk.

26
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,541
It's a burial shroud.

27
00:01:53,625 --> 00:01:54,791
Hmm.

28
00:01:56,291 --> 00:01:57,916
[INKARMAT]
When an elderly Ainu knows

29
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,750
that death is drawing near,

30
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:02,291
they prepare their own
burial shroud.

31
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:03,708
In secret.

32
00:02:05,541 --> 00:02:07,791
Why did you have to say
what you did?

33
00:02:08,791 --> 00:02:12,250
I had no choice but to tell her
what the spirits told me.

34
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:14,583
There is a traitor
close to Asirpa.

35
00:02:15,625 --> 00:02:16,916
[sighs]

36
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,583
[CIKIAPASI]
I don't want Huci to die.

37
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:23,458
She took me in and fed me
when I needed it.

38
00:02:23,541 --> 00:02:25,916
She said the Ainu
always care for children.

39
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,541
She says that without them,

40
00:02:27,625 --> 00:02:29,666
you can't move on
to the next world.

41
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:32,750
Because when an Ainu dies,

42
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:35,666
those left behind perform
a ritual for their souls.

43
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:38,041
Otherwise they can't enter
the afterlife.

44
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,166
So they'll take in
and raise any child,

45
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:44,125
even if they aren't their own.

46
00:02:44,208 --> 00:02:46,250
♪

47
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:50,500
[TANIGAKI]
Cikapasi, don't worry.

48
00:02:51,583 --> 00:02:54,291
I'm gonna bring Asirpa back
safe and sound.

49
00:02:54,375 --> 00:02:56,458
That'll raise Huci's spirits.

50
00:02:56,541 --> 00:02:58,375
So I won't rest until it's done.

51
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:02,125
She took me in, same as you.

52
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:04,166
So I'm one of her kids, too.

53
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,625
No way.

54
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:08,041
You're her gigolo,
Tanigaki Nispa.

55
00:03:08,125 --> 00:03:10,208
-He sure is.
-[BOTH laughing]

56
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:13,583
[BOTH sigh]

57
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:16,291
♪

58
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:24,333
[TANIGAKI] Maybe this is
what I've been looking for.

59
00:05:04,291 --> 00:05:05,750
[TANIGAKI]
Lieutenant Tsurumi.

60
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:08,541
Have you ever heard of a food
called kanemochi?

61
00:05:09,583 --> 00:05:12,500
It's an emergency ration
we Ani Matagi use.

62
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:15,000
One's shaped like a ball
and one's an oval.

63
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:17,083
We take them into
the mountains with us.

64
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:19,958
Supposedly,
the round one is the sun

65
00:05:20,041 --> 00:05:21,916
and the oval is the moon.

66
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,916
Kanemochi, huh?

67
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,291
No, I can't say
I've heard of it.

68
00:05:26,375 --> 00:05:29,708
How's it taste?
Like any other mochi?

69
00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:31,625
[TANIGAKI]
We add water to rice powder,

70
00:05:31,708 --> 00:05:33,708
then mix in miso or salt.

71
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:35,750
Knead thoroughly,
wrap it up in a leaf,

72
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:37,625
then bake it in a covered pan.

73
00:05:38,875 --> 00:05:40,333
Tozawa Matagi, however,

74
00:05:40,416 --> 00:05:43,083
are forbidden from adding miso
to their kanemochi.

75
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:44,416
[TSURUMI]
So each village

76
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:46,708
has its own
particular rules, then?

77
00:05:48,541 --> 00:05:51,000
My father was incredibly stern,

78
00:05:51,083 --> 00:05:53,750
so I never told anybody
about this.

79
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:56,916
But I didn't actually
follow the rules.

80
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,833
I did something special
to my kanemochi.

81
00:05:59,916 --> 00:06:03,958
Then one day, another Matagi
discovered my secret.

82
00:06:04,041 --> 00:06:06,583
[laughs]
How'd he do that?

83
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,208
That's kind of a story.

84
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:11,875
We were hunting a wild goat
that we call an "aoshishi."

85
00:06:13,166 --> 00:06:14,916
Matagi travel in small groups

86
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,125
and each member has a specific
role to play in the hunt.

87
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:24,333
There's a scout, a mukaimatte,
who gives orders to the group.

88
00:06:24,416 --> 00:06:27,083
Then, two riflemen
called matsumai.

89
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:30,625
And two seko who aren't
allowed to use guns.

90
00:06:30,708 --> 00:06:32,583
The seko's main job
is to be loud

91
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:35,041
and drive the prey
into the riflemen's sights.

92
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:39,291
Hyah! Hyah!

93
00:06:39,375 --> 00:06:42,083
[TANIGAKI] The bears the Matagi
call "itazu" have a tendency

94
00:06:42,166 --> 00:06:44,208
to run uphill
into the mountains.

95
00:06:44,291 --> 00:06:46,833
So the seko drive them
toward the peak.

96
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:48,375
The aoshishi are the opposite,

97
00:06:48,458 --> 00:06:50,583
so we drive them away
from the peaks.

98
00:06:50,666 --> 00:06:53,708
I was a seko, out with a boy
a year older than me

99
00:06:53,791 --> 00:06:55,708
named Kenkichi Aoyama.

100
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:59,541
When we got up to the peak,
the weather suddenly changed.

101
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:02,458
♪

102
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:06,583
We sought refuge in a cave,
but the blizzard kept raging.

103
00:07:06,666 --> 00:07:08,583
We were trapped there for days.

104
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,625
The beans and rice
we'd brought weren't enough.

105
00:07:10,708 --> 00:07:12,291
They ran out fast.

106
00:07:13,958 --> 00:07:15,916
Kanemochi was created
to keep you alive

107
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,875
in situations like that.

108
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:20,375
No matter how cold it gets,
it doesn't freeze,

109
00:07:20,458 --> 00:07:22,125
and it never spoils.

110
00:07:22,208 --> 00:07:25,291
And nibbling on just a little
of it is enough to fill you up.

111
00:07:25,375 --> 00:07:26,958
[wind howling]

112
00:07:29,375 --> 00:07:30,416
Here.

113
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:32,958
[scoffs]

114
00:07:33,041 --> 00:07:34,291
What's wrong?

115
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:37,500
I was just thinking that
if this blizzard doesn't stop,

116
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:39,000
this could be our last meal.

117
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:41,166
Ha! Speak for yourself.

118
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:44,083
I'm surviving this even if
it means I have to eat you.

119
00:07:49,208 --> 00:07:51,458
Hey, what's that taste?

120
00:07:51,541 --> 00:07:52,625
Did you mix something in?

121
00:07:52,708 --> 00:07:54,083
[gasps]

122
00:07:54,166 --> 00:07:55,916
The flavor's familiar.

123
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:56,958
-Uh--
-Wait.

124
00:07:57,041 --> 00:07:59,250
Don't tell me. I'll guess it.

125
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,208
Uh, let's see.

126
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:05,166
I know.

127
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:06,375
It's walnuts.

128
00:08:06,458 --> 00:08:08,708
You put walnuts in, didn't you?

129
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:11,541
Yeah, but do me favor.

130
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:13,000
Don't tell my father, okay?

131
00:08:13,083 --> 00:08:15,250
[laughing]

132
00:08:17,666 --> 00:08:19,916
-Hey, Genjirou.
-Huh?

133
00:08:22,291 --> 00:08:24,250
We're going to get
out of this alive.

134
00:08:26,291 --> 00:08:27,458
Hmm.

135
00:08:40,791 --> 00:08:42,541
[TANIGAKI]
Not too long after that,

136
00:08:42,625 --> 00:08:45,208
Kenkichi married
my younger sister, Fumi.

137
00:08:45,291 --> 00:08:47,291
So then, we were like
real brothers.

138
00:08:47,375 --> 00:08:48,583
Mm-hmm.

139
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:53,125
[TANIGAKI] Fumi and Kenkichi
lived quietly and happily,

140
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:55,583
just a little ways
up the mountain, on their own.

141
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:57,375
Away from the village.

142
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:00,416
[grunting]

143
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,250
On that day,

144
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:06,583
I'd been making kanemochi
at home as usual.

145
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:09,041
My brother came in from outside,

146
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:11,625
with a look on his face
I'd never seen before.

147
00:09:11,708 --> 00:09:12,875
-[footsteps approaching]
-Hmm?

148
00:09:12,958 --> 00:09:14,375
[MAN]
It's Fumi.

149
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:16,875
[TANIGAKI] When I saw
the sheer panic in his eyes,

150
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:19,541
it felt like I'd been stabbed
through the chest.

151
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:21,208
[TANIGAKI panting]

152
00:09:22,875 --> 00:09:24,666
By the time I arrived,

153
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:27,666
the little hut where the two
of them lived was already...

154
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:32,833
[panting]

155
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:35,375
♪

156
00:09:40,041 --> 00:09:42,375
I found her body inside.

157
00:09:42,458 --> 00:09:44,958
It was burned to a crisp.

158
00:09:45,041 --> 00:09:46,916
But why?

159
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:47,958
[pants]

160
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:49,250
What happened here?

161
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:51,541
What the hell happened here?!

162
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:52,750
Fumi!

163
00:09:55,583 --> 00:09:58,666
That's when I saw
the stab wound in her heart.

164
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:01,125
♪

165
00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:07,166
And next to her,
Kenkichi's masuke.

166
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:11,625
The short blade we call a masuke
is the soul of a Matagi.

167
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:15,541
But Kenkichi wasn't there.

168
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:17,291
He was nowhere to be found.

169
00:10:19,916 --> 00:10:21,500
Where the hell is he?!

170
00:10:21,583 --> 00:10:23,583
I swear, our son
hasn't been here.

171
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:24,916
-Please don't hurt us.
-[WOMAN crying]

172
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,291
You're not hiding him, are you?!

173
00:10:27,375 --> 00:10:28,875
[crying]

174
00:10:30,791 --> 00:10:35,041
I searched for him everywhere,
but I never found him.

175
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:38,958
And then one day,
I finally heard a rumor

176
00:10:39,041 --> 00:10:42,625
that he'd joined the Seventh
in Hokkaido, and I was ready.

177
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:46,791
[TANIGAKI'S FATHER]
Give it up, Genjirou.

178
00:10:46,875 --> 00:10:49,750
Don't abandon
Ani simply for revenge.

179
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:52,750
Do you really want to waste
your life like that?

180
00:10:55,791 --> 00:10:57,166
[grunting]

181
00:10:58,166 --> 00:11:01,125
I refuse to let
my sister's murderer live!

182
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:03,291
Forget being a Matagi, then.

183
00:11:03,375 --> 00:11:04,916
I won't be back.

184
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:09,666
There were a total
of 37 Tondenhei villages

185
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:10,958
in Hokkaido at that point.

186
00:11:11,041 --> 00:11:13,625
Between my training
and farm work,

187
00:11:13,708 --> 00:11:16,125
it was easy to move around
and search for Kenkichi.

188
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:18,916
But I had no luck.

189
00:11:20,208 --> 00:11:22,416
Then, just before
we left for war,

190
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:25,833
my brother sent me a message
saying my mother was dead.

191
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:30,166
Fumi's brutal death.

192
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:33,541
Me abandoning my home
to go to war.

193
00:11:33,625 --> 00:11:36,541
These things were too much
for her frail heart.

194
00:11:36,625 --> 00:11:38,541
She became sick and died.

195
00:11:41,875 --> 00:11:43,833
My hatred grew as I told myself

196
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:46,875
Kenkichi was responsible
for everything.

197
00:11:46,958 --> 00:11:48,625
If I went to Port Arthur,

198
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:51,666
where the Hokkaido soldiers
were gathered, I could find him.

199
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:54,625
Once I had, I'd wait
for my chance in battle...

200
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,958
and shoot him from behind.

201
00:12:04,208 --> 00:12:05,750
[yelling]

202
00:12:13,916 --> 00:12:15,666
[grunts]

203
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:16,958
[sighs]

204
00:12:19,458 --> 00:12:20,916
[TANIGAKI]
I saw a haggard-looking man

205
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:23,333
sitting in the corner
of one of the trenches.

206
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:26,708
His face was so covered
in blood,

207
00:12:26,791 --> 00:12:29,916
whether it was his
or an enemy's was hard to tell.

208
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:32,166
A white sash.

209
00:12:33,583 --> 00:12:36,708
This man must be a survivor
of last night's suicide charge.

210
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:39,541
That's impressive.

211
00:12:41,625 --> 00:12:43,750
Hey, man, any chance
you got food?

212
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:45,291
[gasps]

213
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:46,833
Um, yeah.

214
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:48,833
Eat.

215
00:12:50,875 --> 00:12:52,500
I appreciate it.

216
00:12:52,583 --> 00:12:53,833
Thanks a lot.

217
00:12:57,375 --> 00:12:59,000
This firm texture.

218
00:12:59,083 --> 00:13:00,625
Could it be mochi?

219
00:13:00,708 --> 00:13:02,625
And I taste miso.

220
00:13:02,708 --> 00:13:05,083
So what is this,
some kind of Akita dish?

221
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,833
How did you know that?

222
00:13:07,916 --> 00:13:09,583
Not hard to deduce.

223
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:10,708
Dead giveaway?

224
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:12,375
The use of these spices.

225
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:15,083
It's definitely an Akita thing.

226
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:16,833
There was a private
in the First Division,

227
00:13:16,916 --> 00:13:19,791
where I'm from, who came from
a place called Ani in Akita.

228
00:13:21,416 --> 00:13:23,583
He talked about it all the time.

229
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:25,875
He told me that he had been
a hunter back home

230
00:13:25,958 --> 00:13:28,416
before he came to Tokyo.

231
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,083
[TANIGAKI]
It was Kenkichi.

232
00:13:31,791 --> 00:13:34,166
I'd finally found
my sister's killer.

233
00:13:36,125 --> 00:13:37,625
That's what had happened.

234
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:41,166
He'd gone to Tokyo
rather than Hokkaido.

235
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:44,208
The soldiers at 203 Hill
were from everywhere,

236
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:46,750
many hailed from
the Hokkaido Seventh,

237
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:51,458
as well as the Shikoku Eleventh,
also the Kanazawa Ninth.

238
00:13:51,541 --> 00:13:54,500
And, yes, there were many
from the Tokyo first.

239
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:57,291
[TANIGAKI]
Yes, and the way I saw it,

240
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:59,083
the gods had finally
helped me discover

241
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:01,166
my little sister's killer.

242
00:14:01,250 --> 00:14:03,250
That's how it felt.

243
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:06,208
I wanted to go
and find him immediately,

244
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:08,375
but I knew that if I saw him,

245
00:14:08,458 --> 00:14:11,000
I'd most likely lose control.

246
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:12,916
I had a good plan.

247
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,083
I knew I could satisfy my need
for revenge

248
00:14:15,166 --> 00:14:18,416
in the heat of a battle,
where I wouldn't be caught.

249
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:20,708
But you were there.

250
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:22,500
That hill was a nightmare.

251
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:23,750
[SOLDIERS yelling]

252
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,250
[TANIGAKI]
No time to look for anybody

253
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:27,625
when it's all you can do
just to survive.

254
00:14:28,916 --> 00:14:30,541
[gunfire]

255
00:14:30,625 --> 00:14:33,416
♪

256
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:39,000
The Russians threw
grenades at us.

257
00:14:39,083 --> 00:14:40,958
And we threw them right back.

258
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:42,000
[grunting]

259
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:47,500
[TANIGAKI] As we began to push
them back further and further,

260
00:14:47,583 --> 00:14:49,875
They got desperate
and changed tactics.

261
00:14:49,958 --> 00:14:51,333
Strapped grenades
to their bodies

262
00:14:51,416 --> 00:14:53,000
and jumped in our trenches.

263
00:14:53,083 --> 00:14:55,791
It was hell. I remember.

264
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:57,666
Blood and body parts everywhere.

265
00:14:57,750 --> 00:15:00,833
Just one of them
could take out ten of us.

266
00:15:00,916 --> 00:15:02,541
[TANIGAKI]
And then, another came.

267
00:15:02,625 --> 00:15:04,083
Bring that man down!

268
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:08,166
Two hits from a Type 30
right to the chest.

269
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:09,708
Didn't even slow him down.

270
00:15:09,791 --> 00:15:11,666
[gasps]

271
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:15,583
Suddenly, a lone man emerged,

272
00:15:15,666 --> 00:15:17,666
running out
of one of the trenches.

273
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:22,458
[inaudible]

274
00:15:22,541 --> 00:15:24,458
[TANIGAKI]
Kenkichi!

275
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:26,958
[grunting]

276
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:28,125
[gasps]

277
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:35,958
[TANIGAKI]
It was bad.

278
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:38,291
Kenkichi just barely survived.

279
00:15:41,666 --> 00:15:43,125
At last,

280
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:46,541
the moment I'd been
waiting for had arrived.

281
00:15:46,625 --> 00:15:48,166
Or so I thought.

282
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:50,250
Kenkichi.

283
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,500
I've finally found you.

284
00:15:52,583 --> 00:15:54,916
I'm gonna stab you
straight through your heart.

285
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:57,333
Just like you did to Fumi!

286
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:01,375
Tanigaki!
Come on, he's done for!

287
00:16:01,458 --> 00:16:02,916
He can't even hear you.

288
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,416
His eardrums were
probably destroyed.

289
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:07,291
[heavy breathing]

290
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,500
[gasping]

291
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:16,750
[weakly]
Fumi.

292
00:16:17,916 --> 00:16:18,958
Huh?

293
00:16:27,208 --> 00:16:29,750
[TANIGAKI] The battle seemed
to reach some kind of stalemate,

294
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:34,375
and the whole place
became strangely quiet.

295
00:16:36,958 --> 00:16:39,000
Why?

296
00:16:39,083 --> 00:16:40,416
Tell me!

297
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,250
Why did you kill Fumi?

298
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:45,166
[weakly]
Who-who are you?

299
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:46,500
What's that voice?

300
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:54,625
I don't know who you are,
but can you take a message?

301
00:16:54,708 --> 00:16:57,375
Can you do that for me?

302
00:16:57,458 --> 00:17:00,333
A man named Tanigaki in Ani.

303
00:17:00,416 --> 00:17:01,500
[gasps]

304
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:03,791
My brother.

305
00:17:03,875 --> 00:17:07,083
I married the Tanigaki
family's daughter, Fumi.

306
00:17:08,583 --> 00:17:10,666
She was so beautiful.

307
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:12,416
Such a warm heart.

308
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,583
Far too good for me.

309
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:18,500
The two of us lived quietly
together in the mountains.

310
00:17:19,708 --> 00:17:21,541
Then one day,

311
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:23,500
she became sick with smallpox.

312
00:17:23,583 --> 00:17:24,750
[gasps]

313
00:17:26,166 --> 00:17:27,625
My parents.

314
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:29,458
Don't tell them.

315
00:17:29,541 --> 00:17:31,500
I'm begging you.

316
00:17:31,583 --> 00:17:32,708
Fumi.

317
00:17:32,791 --> 00:17:35,333
If you do, they'll just worry.

318
00:17:35,416 --> 00:17:37,666
And then they'll try
to come here.

319
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:40,166
If it spreads to them...

320
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:42,333
I know.

321
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:43,333
And you.

322
00:17:43,416 --> 00:17:45,791
You can't stay here, either.

323
00:17:45,875 --> 00:17:48,125
Wha...
What are you trying to say?

324
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:50,875
We'll die together, I swear.

325
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:56,208
When a member of a mountain
family catches smallpox,

326
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:59,833
we abandon that loved one
so it won't spread.

327
00:17:59,916 --> 00:18:03,625
But I couldn't.
I couldn't do it.

328
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:07,750
I'd heard an awful story
about animals finding their way

329
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:09,500
into an abandoned home

330
00:18:09,583 --> 00:18:12,250
and killing the sick
who were left inside.

331
00:18:13,875 --> 00:18:15,666
I knew there was no way

332
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:18,166
I'd let her die alone
in that house.

333
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:21,041
But she refused
to let me stay with her.

334
00:18:22,708 --> 00:18:27,333
If it was known that a Tanigaki
had gotten smallpox,

335
00:18:27,416 --> 00:18:29,791
the rest of the village
would shun them.

336
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:33,833
The other Matagi
would refuse to hunt

337
00:18:33,916 --> 00:18:36,541
with the rest of her family.

338
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:39,333
She wanted me to kill her

339
00:18:39,416 --> 00:18:42,583
then leave without telling
anyone in the village.

340
00:18:42,666 --> 00:18:43,666
So...

341
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:46,958
[crying quietly]

342
00:18:47,041 --> 00:18:50,625
[KENKICHI] She covered
her beautiful face with a cloth,

343
00:18:50,708 --> 00:18:53,000
and then, she said...

344
00:18:54,041 --> 00:18:57,166
If it doesn't spread to you...

345
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:59,708
[KENKICHI and FUMI]
...then, you must decide.

346
00:18:59,791 --> 00:19:03,208
[FUMI] How to spend
the rest of your life.

347
00:19:03,291 --> 00:19:06,416
Find your role, love.

348
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:09,500
I'll try.

349
00:19:12,125 --> 00:19:15,541
At last, I finally did it.

350
00:19:18,208 --> 00:19:23,333
We decided on a way for her
to suffer as little as possible.

351
00:19:23,416 --> 00:19:25,166
I am a hunter.

352
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:28,375
So I used the method
I knew best.

353
00:19:31,125 --> 00:19:32,958
♪

354
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,833
I did what she said.

355
00:19:36,916 --> 00:19:41,083
Burned down our home,
and left the village

356
00:19:41,166 --> 00:19:44,541
without telling her family
about her death.

357
00:19:45,875 --> 00:19:47,291
Ever since,

358
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:51,625
I've spent the rest of my life
bearing the guilt.

359
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:55,500
My actions have caused
great pain

360
00:19:55,583 --> 00:19:58,750
to her family
and to the village.

361
00:20:00,125 --> 00:20:02,916
If I can heal those wounds
in any way...

362
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:05,833
Please, sir.

363
00:20:05,916 --> 00:20:11,750
Please, tell this story
to Tanigaki in Ani.

364
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:12,833
Please.

365
00:20:12,916 --> 00:20:15,250
♪

366
00:20:22,208 --> 00:20:23,333
[gasps]

367
00:20:26,041 --> 00:20:29,125
Kanemochi with walnuts.

368
00:20:31,583 --> 00:20:33,291
Genjirou.

369
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:41,750
[TANIGAKI] And then, he passed
from this life before my eyes.

370
00:20:44,916 --> 00:20:46,833
He had found his role in life

371
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:50,916
and spent the rest of his days
carrying it out.

372
00:20:51,916 --> 00:20:54,791
Every day since, I ask myself
the same question,

373
00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:57,416
"What is my role in life?"

374
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:59,416
I can't go back to Ani now.

375
00:21:00,583 --> 00:21:03,125
I couldn't bear to face
my father or brother.

376
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:06,833
Tanigaki.

377
00:21:06,916 --> 00:21:09,333
Perhaps I can help you
answer your question.

378
00:21:09,416 --> 00:21:10,500
Hmm?

379
00:21:13,041 --> 00:21:16,333
Hey, I know what you can do
for a start.

380
00:21:16,416 --> 00:21:19,708
How about some of those
kanemochi with walnuts?

381
00:21:24,791 --> 00:21:26,541
At your service, sir.

382
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:34,583
[birds squawking]

383
00:21:40,875 --> 00:21:43,250
-[CIKIAPASI] Hey, look at that.
-Hmm?

384
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:45,625
Somebody's dancing
all the way out there.

385
00:21:45,708 --> 00:21:47,583
Doesn't it look like Asirpa?

386
00:21:47,666 --> 00:21:48,666
Hmm.

387
00:21:57,083 --> 00:21:58,250
Nice.

388
00:21:58,333 --> 00:22:00,916
This is a dance
from Kushiro, right?

389
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,541
[ASIRPA]
The sarorunrimse.

390
00:22:02,625 --> 00:22:03,958
The crane dance.

391
00:22:11,750 --> 00:22:13,458
Hmm. Look, someone's coming.

392
00:22:13,541 --> 00:22:14,541
Uh...

393
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,291
[gasps]

394
00:22:20,916 --> 00:22:21,791
You see?

395
00:22:21,875 --> 00:22:23,625
I knew it, it's Asirpa!

396
00:22:24,875 --> 00:22:27,125
[ASIRPA]
Cikapasi and Cironnup.

397
00:22:27,208 --> 00:22:28,875
And Tanigaki.

398
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,666
How in the world?

399
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:10,416
[NARRATOR]
Next Time, "Kamuy Hopunire."

